CYP389B1 was expressed by using the method of homologous recombination (Feng et al., 2019). Primers details used for protein expression are listed in Table S1. pColdII DNA was selected as the prokaryotic expression vector, and BamHI (upstream) and HindIII (downstream) on the vector were selected to construct recombinant plasmid. The recombinant plasmid was transformed into BL21 (DE3) cells to express recombinant protein. The target protein was extracted and purified. Part of the protein was subjected to SDS-page and Western blot experiments, and the rest was stored at −80 °C (Jeong et al., 2018). The kinetic parameters were analyzed by setting five concentration gradients of fenpropathrin to the recombinant protein CYP389B1. The Michaelis constant (K

                           m
                        ) and the maximum reaction rate (V

                           max
                        ) were determined by double reciprocal mapping, in which the reaction system was recombined. Protein and CPR protein content was set as 1:1. The detection method of P450 activity was consistent with enzyme activity measurements.

